    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n               <jats:p>We show that a change in organizational structure from partnerships to public companies\u2014which weakens contractual commitment\u2014can lead to higher investment in high return-and-risk activities, higher productivity (value added per employee) and greater income dispersion (inequality). These predictions are consistent with the observed evolution of the financial sector where the switch from partnerships to public companies has been especially important in the decades that preceded the 21st Century financial crisis.</jats:p>",
